.TH GAT-RM 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-rm \- remove a linked worktree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat rm
.I <ticket>
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B gat remove
.I <ticket>
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B gat delete
.I <ticket>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Removes a worktree via native Git. Refuses to remove the primary worktree, a
locked worktree (without
.BR \-\-force ),
or a dirty worktree (without
.BR \-\-force ).
Optionally deletes the branch afterward. Cleans up the worktree's usage metadata
entry. By default prompts for confirmation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Remove a dirty or locked worktree.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip the confirmation prompt.
.TP
.B \-\-delete\-branch
Delete the branch after removal (must be merged).
.TP
.B \-\-force\-delete\-branch
Force-delete the branch (implies
.BR \-\-delete\-branch ).
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show the planned removal only.
.TP
.BI \-\-prefix " prefix" ", " \-\-no\-prefix
Ticket prefix handling.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json"
Output format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat rm 12345
gat rm 12345 \-\-yes \-\-delete\-branch
gat rm 12345 \-\-force \-\-yes
gat delete 12345 \-\-dry\-run
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-archive (1),
.BR gat\-merge (1)
